### Overview

- Most of the time, I don't access raw geospatial data
- Instead, I use packages to access the data

### Global Data

#### Packages

- {rnaturalearth}
- {rgeoboundaries}

::: {.notes}
Boundaries are political

Talk about how each package handles disputed territories

https://www.naturalearthdata.com/about/disputed-boundaries-policy/

https://www.andrewheiss.com/blog/2025/02/13/natural-earth-crimea/#natural-earth-de-jure-points-of-view
:::

#### {rnaturalearth}

---


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(rnaturalearth)
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
all_countries <-
  ne_countries(scale = "small")
```
:::


---


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(mapview)

all_countries |>
  mapview()
```
:::


---


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
africa <-
  ne_countries(continent = "Africa")
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
africa |>
  mapview()
```
:::


---


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ukraine <-
  ne_countries(country = "Ukraine")
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ukraine |>
  mapview()
```
:::


#### {rgeoboundaries}

::: {.notes}
Show https://www.geoboundaries.org/

https://github.com/wmgeolab/rgeoboundaries
:::

---


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(rgeoboundaries)
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
all_countries_v2 <-
  geoboundaries(adm_lvl = 0)
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
all_countries_v2 |>
  mapview()
```
:::


---


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ukraine_v2 <-
  geoboundaries(country = "Ukraine")
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ukraine_v2 |>
  mapview()
```
:::


---


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
geoboundaries(
  country = "Ukraine",
  adm_lvl = 1
) |>
  mapview()
```
:::


---


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
geoboundaries(
  country = "Ukraine",
  adm_lvl = 2
) |>
  mapview()
```
:::


::: {.notes}
Can go down to 5 levels; see https://github.com/wmgeolab/rgeoboundaries/blob/master/R/geoboundaries.R#L57C1-L62C87
:::

### US Data

- {tigris}
- {tidycensus}

#### {tigris}


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(tigris)
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
us_states <-
  states()
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
us_states
```
:::


